InterfaceIndex.name: InterfaceIndex
InterfaceIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface or interface sub-layer in the managed system. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub- layer must remain constant at least from one re- initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

TmnxPortID.name: TmnxPortID
TmnxPortID.description: A portid is an unique 32 bit number encoded as shown below. 32 30 | 29 26 | 25 22 | 21 16 | 15 1 | +-----+-------+-------+-------+-------+ |000 | slot | mda | port | zero | Physical Port +-----+-------+-------+-------+-------+ 32 30 | 29 26 | 25 22 | 21 16 | 15 1 | +-----+-------+-------+-------+-------+ |001 | slot | mda | port |channel| Channel +-----+-------+-------+-------+-------+ Slots, mdas (if present), ports, and channels are numbered starting with 1. 32 29 | 28 10 | 9 1 | +---------+-------------------+-------+ | 0 1 0 0 | zeros | ID | Virtual Port +---------+-------------------+-------+ 32 29 | 28 9 | 8 1 | +---------+---------------------+-----+ | 0 1 0 1 | zeros | ID | LAG Port +---------+---------------------+-----+ A card port number (cpn) has significance within the context of the card on which it resides(ie., cpn 2 may exist in one or more cards in the chassis). Whereas, portid is an unique/absolute port number (apn) within a given chassis. An 'invalid portid' is a TmnxPortID with a value of 0x1e000000 as represented below. 32 30 | 29 26 | 25 22 | 21 16 | 15 1 | +-----+-------+-------+-------+-------+ |zero | ones | zero | zero | zero | Invalid Port +-----+-------+-------+-------+-------+

TmnxEncapVal.name: TmnxEncapVal
TmnxEncapVal.description: The value of the label used to identify the entity using the specified encapsulation value on a specific port. The format of this object depends on the encapsulation type defined on this port. When the encapsulation is nullEncap the value of this object must be zero. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00000000 00000000 00000000 00000000| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ When the encapsulation is dot1qEncap the value of this object is equal to the 12-bit IEEE 802.1Q VLAN ID. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00000000 00000000 0000XXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ When the encapsulation is mplsEncap the value of this object is equal to the 20-bit LSP ID. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00000000 0000XXXX XXXXXXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ When the encapsulation is frEncap, the value of this object is equal to the 10-bit Frame Relay DLCI. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00000000 00000000 000000XX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ When the encapsulation is qinqEncap, the value of the outer 802.1Q VLAN ID is encoded in the least significant 16 bits, and the value of the inner VLAN ID is encoded in the most significant 16 bits. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |0000YYYY YYYYYYYY 0000XXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ When the encapsulation is atmEncap, the value of the ATM VCI is encoded in the least significant 16 bits, and the value of the ATM VPI is encoded in the next 12 bits. For ATM VCs, the top 3 bits are 000. The value of the ATM VCI is encoded in the least significant 16 bits, and the value of the ATM VPI is encoded in the next 12 bits. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |0000YYYY YYYYYYYY XXXXXXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ For ATM capture VCs, bits 0 and 28 are 1. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00010000 00000000 00000000 00000001| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ For ATM VPs, the top 3 bits are 010. The value of the ATM VPI is encoded in the least significant 12 bits. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |01000000 00000000 0000XXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ For ATM VP ranges, the top 3 bits are 100. The value of the start of the ATM VPI range is encoded in the least significant 12 bits, and the value of the end of the ATM VP range is encoded in the next 12 bits. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |10000000 YYYYYYYY YYYYXXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ For ATM ports, the top 3 bits are 110, and the rest of the bits must be zero. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |11000000 00000000 00000000 00000000| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ For ATM CPs, the top 3 bits are 001. The value of the ATM CP is encoded in the least significant 13 bits. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00100000 00000000 000XXXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ When the encapsulation is wanMirrorEncap the value of this object is equal to the 12-bit value. 31 0 +--------+--------+--------+--------+ |00000000 00000000 0000XXXX XXXXXXXX| +--------+--------+--------+--------+ Some ports have a restrictions to the encapsulation types that they can support and hence impose restrictions on the respective formats defined above.

QTag.name: QTag
QTag.description: The QTag data type is a 12-bit integer tag used to identify a service. The values 0 and 4095 are not allowed.

QTagOrZero.name: QTagOrZero
QTagOrZero.description: The data type QTagOrZero represents a VLAN tag. The value '0' indicates that no VLAN tag is provisioned, or that its value is unknown.

QTagFullRange.name: QTagFullRange
QTagFullRange.description: The data type QTagFullRange represents a VLAN tag. A VLAN tag is 12 bits is size. The data type QTagFullRange covers the whole range of possible values. (0..4095 or 0x0 .. 0xFFF)

QTagFullRangeOrNone.name: QTagFullRangeOrNone
QTagFullRangeOrNone.description: The data type QTagFullRangeOrNone represents a VLAN tag. A VLAN tag is 12 bits is size. The data type QTagFullRange covers the whole range of possible values. (0..4095 or 0x0 .. 0xFFF). The value '-1' indicates the absense of a VLAN tag.

TmnxStrSapId.name: TmnxStrSapId
TmnxStrSapId.description: The value of TmnxStrSapId is a printable string which contains the owner SAP Id or equivalent on a remote system. The string should contain the printable string equivalent of the textual-conventions TmnxPortID and TmnxEncapVal in the format specified as TmnxPortID[:TmnxEncapVal]

IpAddressPrefixLength.name: IpAddressPrefixLength
IpAddressPrefixLength.description: the number of bits to match in an IP address mask.

TmnxActionType.name: TmnxActionType
TmnxActionType.description: The TmnxActionType data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to support action or operation style commands. Setting a variable of this type to 'doAction' causes the action to occur. GETs and GETNEXTs on this variable return 'not-applicable'.

TmnxAdminState.name: TmnxAdminState
TmnxAdminState.description: The TmnxAdminState data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the administratively desired state of functional modules.

TmnxOperState.name: TmnxOperState
TmnxOperState.description: The TmnxOperState data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the current operational state of functional modules.

TmnxStatus.name: TmnxStatus
TmnxStatus.description: The TmnxStatus data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the current status of functional modules in the system such as OSPF and MPLS protocols. Setting this variable to 'create' causes instantiation of the feature in the system. Setting it to 'delete' removes the instance and all associated configuration information.

TmnxEnabledDisabled.name: TmnxEnabledDisabled
TmnxEnabledDisabled.description: The TmnxEnabledDisabled data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify whether an entity is 'enabled' or 'disabled'.

TmnxEnabledDisabledOrInherit.name: TmnxEnabledDisabledOrInherit
TmnxEnabledDisabledOrInherit.description: The TmnxEnabledDisabledOrInherit data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify whether an entity is 'enabled', 'disabled' or inherits its state from another object that is usually in another mib table.

TNamedItem.name: TNamedItem
TNamedItem.description: The name of an item. When used as an index to a table, the item name uniquely identifies the instance. When used in a reference (TNamedItemOrEmpty) the item name entry must exist in the table. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TNamedItemOrEmpty.name: TNamedItemOrEmpty
TNamedItemOrEmpty.description: The name of an item, or an empty string. When used in a reference (TNamedItemOrEmpty) the item name entry must exist in the table. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TLNamedItem.name: TLNamedItem
TLNamedItem.description: The long name of an item. When used as an index to a table, the item name uniquely identifies the instance. When used in a reference (TLNamedItemOrEmpty) the item name entry must exist in the table. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TLNamedItemOrEmpty.name: TLNamedItemOrEmpty
TLNamedItemOrEmpty.description: The long name of an item, or an empty string. When used in a reference (TLNamedItemOrEmpty) the item name entry must exist in the table. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TItemDescription.name: TItemDescription
TItemDescription.description: Description for an item. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TItemLongDescription.name: TItemLongDescription
TItemLongDescription.description: Longer description for an item. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc.

TmnxVRtrID.name: TmnxVRtrID
TmnxVRtrID.description: A number used to identify a virtual router instance in the system.

TmnxVRtrIDOrZero.name: TmnxVRtrIDOrZero
TmnxVRtrIDOrZero.description: A number used to identify a virtual router instance in the system. The number 0 will have special significance in the context the TC is used.

TmnxCustId.name: TmnxCustId
TmnxCustId.description: A number used to identify a Customer or Subscriber. This ID must be unique within the Service Domain. The value 0 is used as the null ID.

BgpPeeringStatus.name: BgpPeeringStatus
BgpPeeringStatus.description: The status of the BGP peering session.

TmnxServId.name: TmnxServId
TmnxServId.description: A number used to identify a Service. This ID must be unique within the Service Domain. The value 0 is used as the null ID.

ServiceAdminStatus.name: ServiceAdminStatus
ServiceAdminStatus.description: ServiceAdminStatus data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the administrative state of a service.

ServiceOperStatus.name: ServiceOperStatus
ServiceOperStatus.description: ServiceOperStatus data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the current operational state of a service.

TPolicyID.name: TPolicyID
TPolicyID.description: The identification number of a policy.

TTmplPolicyID.name: TTmplPolicyID
TTmplPolicyID.description: The identification number of a policy for template objects.

TSapIngressPolicyID.name: TSapIngressPolicyID
TSapIngressPolicyID.description: The identification number of a SAP ingress policy.

TSapEgressPolicyID.name: TSapEgressPolicyID
TSapEgressPolicyID.description: The identification number of a SAP egress policy.

TSdpIngressPolicyID.name: TSdpIngressPolicyID
TSdpIngressPolicyID.description: The identification number of a SDP ingress network policy.

TSdpEgressPolicyID.name: TSdpEgressPolicyID
TSdpEgressPolicyID.description: The identification number of a SDP egress network policy.

TQosQGrpInstanceIDorZero.name: TQosQGrpInstanceIDorZero
TQosQGrpInstanceIDorZero.description: The identifcation number of a QoS queue group instance. The value of '0' indicates the system determined default value.

TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyId.name: TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyId
TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyId.description: TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyId identifies a transit IP policy.

TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyIdOrZero.name: TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyIdOrZero
TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyIdOrZero.description: TmnxBsxTransitIpPolicyId identifies a transit ip policy. The value '0' indicates an invalid transit IP policy.

TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyId.name: TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyId
TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyId.description: TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyId identifies a transit prefix policy.

TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyIdOrZero.name: TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyIdOrZero
TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyIdOrZero.description: TmnxBsxTransPrefPolicyId identifies a transit prefix policy. The value '0' indicates an invalid transit prefix policy.

TmnxBsxAarpId.name: TmnxBsxAarpId
TmnxBsxAarpId.description: TmnxBsxAarpId identifies an instance of the AA Redundancy Protocol (AARP).

TmnxBsxAarpIdOrZero.name: TmnxBsxAarpIdOrZero
TmnxBsxAarpIdOrZero.description: TmnxBsxAarpIdOrZero identifies an instance of the AA Redundancy Protocol (AARP). The value of '0' indicates an invalid AARP instance.

TmnxBsxAarpServiceRefType.name: TmnxBsxAarpServiceRefType
TmnxBsxAarpServiceRefType.description: TmnxBsxAarpServiceRefType identifies the role of the SAP or Spoke SDP service point being referenced by an AARP instance. This reference is made in the context of a AARP instance identified by TmnxBsxAarpIdOrZero. The service reference types are: none(0) - service reference type is not applicable. dualHomed(1) - the service reference point is a SAP or Spoke SDP connected into a dually homed network being protected by the AARP instance. shuntSubscriberSide(2) - the service reference point is a Spoke SDP acting as a subscriber side shunt used by the AARP instance. A subscriber side shunt carries the local from/to subscriber traffic when AA is performed remotely. shuntNetworkSide(3) - the service reference point is a Spoke SDP acting as a network side shunt used by the AARP instance. A network side shunt carries the local from/to network traffic when AA is performed remotely. For the case when TmnxBsxAarpIdOrZero refers to the invalid AARP instance '0', the service reference type is 'none(0)'.

TSapEgrEncapGrpQosPolicyIdOrZero.name: TSapEgrEncapGrpQosPolicyIdOrZero
TSapEgrEncapGrpQosPolicyIdOrZero.description: TSapEgrEncapGrpQosPolicyIdOrZero identifies SAP egress Encapsulation group QoS policy. The value '0' indicates no QoS policy is set.

TSapEgrEncapGroupType.name: TSapEgrEncapGroupType
TSapEgrEncapGroupType.description: TSapEgrEncapGroupType identifies Encapsulation group type on SAP egress.

TSapEgrEncapGroupActionType.name: TSapEgrEncapGroupActionType
TSapEgrEncapGroupActionType.description: TSapEgrEncapGroupActionType identifies Encapsulation group action type on SAP egress. It is used to create or destroy row entries in an associated table.

TPerPacketOffset.name: TPerPacketOffset
TPerPacketOffset.description: The value, in bytes, of the adjustment to make to the size of each packet for accounting.

TPerPacketOffsetOvr.name: TPerPacketOffsetOvr
TPerPacketOffsetOvr.description: The value, in bytes, of the override of the adjustment to make to the size of each packet for accounting. A value of -128 indicates no override.

TIngressHsmdaPerPacketOffset.name: TIngressHsmdaPerPacketOffset
TIngressHsmdaPerPacketOffset.description: The value, in bytes, of the adjustment to make to the size of each incoming packet for accounting.

TEgressQPerPacketOffset.name: TEgressQPerPacketOffset
TEgressQPerPacketOffset.description: The value, in bytes, of the adjustment to make to the size of each packet for accounting.

TIngHsmdaPerPacketOffsetOvr.name: TIngHsmdaPerPacketOffsetOvr
TIngHsmdaPerPacketOffsetOvr.description: The value, in bytes, of the override of the adjustment to make to the size of each incoming packet for accounting. A value of -128 indicates no override.

TEgressHsmdaPerPacketOffset.name: TEgressHsmdaPerPacketOffset
TEgressHsmdaPerPacketOffset.description: The value, in bytes, of the adjustment to make to the size of each outgoing packet for accounting.

THsmdaCounterIdOrZero.name: THsmdaCounterIdOrZero
THsmdaCounterIdOrZero.description: The identifcation number of a HSMDA counter. The value 0 indicates an undefined counter id.

THsmdaCounterIdOrZeroOrAll.name: THsmdaCounterIdOrZeroOrAll
THsmdaCounterIdOrZeroOrAll.description: The identifcation number of a HSMDA counter. The value (0) indicates an undefined counter id. The value (-1) is used to indicate all counters.

TEgrHsmdaPerPacketOffsetOvr.name: TEgrHsmdaPerPacketOffsetOvr
TEgrHsmdaPerPacketOffsetOvr.description: The value, in bytes, of the override of the adjustment to make to the size of each outgoing packet for accounting. A value of -128 indicates no override.

TIngressHsmdaCounterId.name: TIngressHsmdaCounterId
TIngressHsmdaCounterId.description: The identifcation number of a HSMDA ingress counter.

TIngressHsmdaCounterIdOrZero.name: TIngressHsmdaCounterIdOrZero
TIngressHsmdaCounterIdOrZero.description: The identifcation number of a HSMDA ingress counter. The value 0 indicates an undefined counter id.

TEgressHsmdaCounterId.name: TEgressHsmdaCounterId
TEgressHsmdaCounterId.description: The identifcation number of a HSMDA egress counter.

TEgressHsmdaCounterIdOrZero.name: TEgressHsmdaCounterIdOrZero
TEgressHsmdaCounterIdOrZero.description: The identifcation number of a HSMDA egress counter. The value 0 indicates an undefined counter id.

TEgrRateModType.name: TEgrRateModType
TEgrRateModType.description: The data type TEgrRateModType represents the type of egress-rate modification that is to be applied.

TPolicyStatementNameOrEmpty.name: TPolicyStatementNameOrEmpty
TPolicyStatementNameOrEmpty.description: The name of a policy statement, when an object refers to it.

TmnxVcType.name: TmnxVcType
TmnxVcType.description: The value of TmnxVcType is an enumerated integer that indicates a Virtual Circuit (VC) type. 'frDlciMartini(1)' replaces the old 'frDlci' when used over martini tunnels.

TmnxVcId.name: TmnxVcId
TmnxVcId.description: A 32 bit number is used to identify a VC(Virtual Circuit). The VC ID cannot be 0.

TmnxVcIdOrNone.name: TmnxVcIdOrNone
TmnxVcIdOrNone.description: A 32 bit number is used to identify a VC(Virtual Circuit). A value of 0 indicates no VC ID is configured or available.

Dot1PPriority.name: Dot1PPriority
Dot1PPriority.description: IEEE 802.1p priority. zero is lowest, seven is highest. -1 means not set

Dot1PPriorityMask.name: Dot1PPriorityMask
Dot1PPriorityMask.description: IEEE 802.1p priority mask. zero is lowest, seven is highest.

ServiceAccessPoint.name: ServiceAccessPoint
ServiceAccessPoint.description: 802.2 LLC SAP value, Source and Destination.

TLspExpValue.name: TLspExpValue
TLspExpValue.description: MPLS Experimental bits. -1 means not set.

TIpProtocol.name: TIpProtocol
TIpProtocol.description: IP protocol number. well known protocol numbers include ICMP(1), TCP(6), UDP(17). -1 means value not set. -2 indicates protocol wildcard for UDP and TCP.

TIpOption.name: TIpOption
TIpOption.description: IP packet options octet. explanation of the octet bits: IP OPTION NUMBERS The Internet Protocol (IP) has provision for optional header fields identified by an option type field. Options 0 and 1 are exactly one octet which is their type field. All other options have their one octet type field, followed by a one octet length field, followed by length-2 octets of option data. The option type field is sub-divided into a one bit copied flag, a two bit class field, and a five bit option number. These taken together form an eight bit value for the option type field. IP options are commonly refered to by this value. Copy Class Number Value Name Reference ---- ----- ------ ----- ------------------------------- --------- 0 0 0 0 EOOL - End of Options List [RFC791,JBP] 0 0 1 1 NOP - No Operation [RFC791,JBP] 1 0 2 130 SEC - Security [RFC1108] 1 0 3 131 LSR - Loose Source Route [RFC791,JBP] 0 2 4 68 TS - Time Stamp [RFC791,JBP] 1 0 5 133 E-SEC - Extended Security [RFC1108] 1 0 6 134 CIPSO - Commercial Security [???] 0 0 7 7 RR - Record Route [RFC791,JBP] 1 0 8 136 SID - Stream ID [RFC791,JBP] 1 0 9 137 SSR - Strict Source Route [RFC791,JBP] 0 0 10 10 ZSU - Experimental Measurement [ZSu] 0 0 11 11 MTUP - MTU Probe [RFC1191]* 0 0 12 12 MTUR - MTU Reply [RFC1191]* 1 2 13 205 FINN - Experimental Flow Control [Finn] 1 0 14 142 VISA - Expermental Access Control [Estrin] 0 0 15 15 ENCODE - ??? [VerSteeg] 1 0 16 144 IMITD - IMI Traffic Descriptor [Lee] 1 0 17 145 EIP - Extended Internet Protocol[RFC1385] 0 2 18 82 TR - Traceroute [RFC1393] 1 0 19 147 ADDEXT - Address Extension [Ullmann IPv7] 1 0 20 148 RTRALT - Router Alert [RFC2113] 1 0 21 149 SDB - Selective Directed Broadcast[Graff] 1 0 22 150 NSAPA - NSAP Addresses [Carpenter] 1 0 23 151 DPS - Dynamic Packet State [Malis] 1 0 24 152 UMP - Upstream Multicast Pkt. [Farinacci] [Note, an asterisk (*) denotes an obsoleted IP Option Number.]

TTcpUdpPort.name: TTcpUdpPort
TTcpUdpPort.description: The number of a TCP or UDP port. Well known port numbers include ftp-data(20), ftp(21), telnet(23), smtp(25), http(80), pop3(110), nntp(119), snmp(161), snmptrap(162), etc.

TOperator.name: TOperator
TOperator.description: The operator specifies the manner in which a couple of other MIB objects in the table are supposed to be used. Operator Value1 Value2 ---------------------------------------------------- none(0) Any(0) Any(0) eq(1) Specified Value Any(0) range(2) Starting Value Ending Value lt(3) Specified Value Any(0) gt(4) Specified Value Any(0) 'Any(0)' specifies that, this object can accept any values but would default to 0.

TTcpUdpPortOperator.name: TTcpUdpPortOperator
TTcpUdpPortOperator.description: The operator used for checking on TCP/UDP ports values and ranges

TFrameType.name: TFrameType
TFrameType.description: The type of the frame for which this mac filter match criteria is defined.

TQueueId.name: TQueueId
TQueueId.description: The value of TQueueId specifies the identification number of a queue. A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific queue identification has been assigned for this object. When an object of type TQueueId is an SNMP table index, an index value of zero (0) is not allowed and a noCreation error will be returned.

TQueueIdOrAll.name: TQueueIdOrAll
TQueueIdOrAll.description: The value of TQueueIdOrAll specifies the identification number of a queue A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific queue identification has been assigned for this object. A value of (-1) indicates 'all queues'.

TIngressQueueId.name: TIngressQueueId
TIngressQueueId.description: The value of TIngressQueueId specifies the identification number of an ingress queue. A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific queue identification has been assigned for this object. When an object of type TIngressQueueId is an SNMP table index, an index value of zero (0) is not allowed and a noCreation error will be returned.

TEgressQueueId.name: TEgressQueueId
TEgressQueueId.description: The value of TEgressQueueId specifies the identification number of an egress queue. A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific queue identification has been assigned for this object. When an object of type TEgressQueueId is an SNMP table index, an index value of zero (0) is not allowed and a noCreation error will be returned.

TIngressHsmdaQueueId.name: TIngressHsmdaQueueId
TIngressHsmdaQueueId.description: The value of TIngressHsmdaQueueId specifies the identification number of a HSMDA ingress queue. A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific queue identification has been assigned for this object. When an object of type TIngressHsmdaQueueId is an SNMP table index, an index value of zero (0) is not allowed and a noCreation error will be returned.

TEgressHsmdaQueueId.name: TEgressHsmdaQueueId
TEgressHsmdaQueueId.description: The value of TEgressHsmdaQueueId specifies the identification number of a HSMDA egress queue. A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific queue identification has been assigned for this object. When an object of type TEgressHsmdaQueueId is an SNMP table index, an index value of zero (0) is not allowed and a noCreation error will be returned.

THsmdaSchedulerPolicyGroupId.name: THsmdaSchedulerPolicyGroupId
THsmdaSchedulerPolicyGroupId.description: The value of THsmdaSchedulerPolicyGroupId specifies the identification number of a HSMDA scheduler policy group. A value of zero (0) indicates that no specific group identification has been assigned for this object. When an object of type THsmdaSchedulerPolicyGroupId is an SNMP table index, an index value of zero (0) is not allowed and a noCreation error will be returned.

THsmdaPolicyIncludeQueues.name: THsmdaPolicyIncludeQueues
THsmdaPolicyIncludeQueues.description: The value of THsmdaPolicyIncludeQueues specifies which queues are to be scheduled in the same class in a HSMDA scheduler.

THsmdaPolicyScheduleClass.name: THsmdaPolicyScheduleClass
THsmdaPolicyScheduleClass.description: The value of THsmdaPolicyScheduleClass the class at which the queues specified by THsmdaPolicyIncludeQueues in a HSMDA scheduler.

TDSCPName.name: TDSCPName
TDSCPName.description: The name of a Differential Services Code Point value.

TDSCPNameOrEmpty.name: TDSCPNameOrEmpty
TDSCPNameOrEmpty.description: The name of a Differential Services Code Point value.

TDSCPValue.name: TDSCPValue
TDSCPValue.description: The value of a Differential Services Code Point.

TDSCPValueOrNone.name: TDSCPValueOrNone
TDSCPValueOrNone.description: The value of a Differential Services Code Point (DSCP). A value of -1 means that no DSCP value is configured or available.

TDSCPFilterActionValue.name: TDSCPFilterActionValue
TDSCPFilterActionValue.description: The value of a Differential Services Code Point. -1 means not set.

TFCName.name: TFCName
TFCName.description: The name of a Forwarding Class entry.

TFCNameOrEmpty.name: TFCNameOrEmpty
TFCNameOrEmpty.description: The name of a Forwarding Class entry.

TFCSet.name: TFCSet
TFCSet.description: This data type describes a set of Forwarding Classes.

TFCType.name: TFCType
TFCType.description: This data type enumerates the Forwarding Classes.

TmnxTunnelType.name: TmnxTunnelType
TmnxTunnelType.description: The type of this tunnel entity.

TmnxTunnelID.name: TmnxTunnelID
TmnxTunnelID.description: The identifying value for a BGP-VPRN tunnel. Depending on the tunnel type the associated tunnel-id may be an sdp-id, an lsp-id or zero(0).

TmnxBgpRouteTarget.name: TmnxBgpRouteTarget
TmnxBgpRouteTarget.description: TmnxBgpRouteTarget is an readable string that specifies the extended community name to be accepted by a Route Reflector Server or advertised by the router when reflecting any routes. I.e, it does not apply to routes that are not reflected by the router.

TmnxVPNRouteDistinguisher.name: TmnxVPNRouteDistinguisher
TmnxVPNRouteDistinguisher.description: The VPRN route distinguisher is a 8-octet object. It contains a 2-octet type field followed by a 6-octet value field. The type field specify how to interpret the value field. Type 0 specifies two subfields as a 2-octet administrative field and a 4-octet assigned number subfield. Type 1 specifies two subfields as a 4-octet administrative field which must contain an IP address and a 2-octet assigned number subfield. Type 2 specifies two subfields as a 4-octet administrative field which contains a 4-octet AS number and a 2-octet assigned number subfield.

SdpBindId.name: SdpBindId
SdpBindId.description: The value used to uniquely identify an SDP Binding. The first four octets correspond to the zero-extended 16-bit SDP ID, while the remaining four octets correspond to the 32-bit VC ID, both encoded in network byte order.

TmnxVRtrMplsLspID.name: TmnxVRtrMplsLspID
TmnxVRtrMplsLspID.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each Label Switched Path in the managed system.

TPortSchedulerPIR.name: TPortSchedulerPIR
TPortSchedulerPIR.description: The Peak Information Rate (PIR) rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TPortSchedulerPIRRate.name: TPortSchedulerPIRRate
TPortSchedulerPIRRate.description: The Peak Information Rate (PIR) rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TPortSchedulerCIR.name: TPortSchedulerCIR
TPortSchedulerCIR.description: The Committed Information Rate (CIR) rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TWeight.name: TWeight
TWeight.description: The weight of the specified entity while feeding into the parent.

TNonZeroWeight.name: TNonZeroWeight
TNonZeroWeight.description: The weight of the specified entity while feeding into the parent.

TPolicerWeight.name: TPolicerWeight
TPolicerWeight.description: The relative weight of the specified entity while feeding into the parent.

THsmdaWeight.name: THsmdaWeight
THsmdaWeight.description: The weight of the specified HSMDA entity while feeding into the parent.

THsmdaWrrWeight.name: THsmdaWrrWeight
THsmdaWrrWeight.description: The weight of the specified HSMDA entity while feeding into the parent.

THsmdaWeightClass.name: THsmdaWeightClass
THsmdaWeightClass.description: The weight of the specified HSMDA entity while feeding into the parent.

THsmdaWeightOverride.name: THsmdaWeightOverride
THsmdaWeightOverride.description: The weight of the specified HSMDA entity while feeding into the parent. A value of -2 specifies no override.

THsmdaWrrWeightOverride.name: THsmdaWrrWeightOverride
THsmdaWrrWeightOverride.description: The weight of the specified HSMDA entity while feeding into the parent. A value of -2 specifies no override.

TCIRRate.name: TCIRRate
TCIRRate.description: The CIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THPolCIRRate.name: THPolCIRRate
THPolCIRRate.description: The CIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TRateType.name: TRateType
TRateType.description: The type of the PIR/CIR rate. The value 'kbps' means the rate is specified in kbps. The value 'percent' means the rate is specified in percentage

TBWRateType.name: TBWRateType
TBWRateType.description: The type of the PIR/CIR percent rate. The value 'kbps' means the rate is specified in kbps. The value 'percentPortLimit' means the rate is specified in percentage of port limit. The value 'percentLocalLimit' means the rate is specified in percentage of local limit.

TPolicerRateType.name: TPolicerRateType
TPolicerRateType.description: The type of the PIR/CIR percent rate. The value 'kbps' means the rate is specified in kbps. The value 'percentLocalLimit' means the rate is specified in percentage of local limit.

TCIRRateOverride.name: TCIRRateOverride
TCIRRateOverride.description: The CIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

THPolCIRRateOverride.name: THPolCIRRateOverride
THPolCIRRateOverride.description: The CIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

TCIRPercentOverride.name: TCIRPercentOverride
TCIRPercentOverride.description: The CIR percentage rate specified in hundredths of a percent. A value of -2 specifies no override.

THsmdaCIRKRate.name: THsmdaCIRKRate
THsmdaCIRKRate.description: The HSMDA CIR rate to be used in Kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THsmdaCIRKRateOverride.name: THsmdaCIRKRateOverride
THsmdaCIRKRateOverride.description: The HSMDA CIR rate to be used in Kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

THsmdaCIRMRate.name: THsmdaCIRMRate
THsmdaCIRMRate.description: The HSMDA CIR rate to be used in Mbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THsmdaCIRMRateOverride.name: THsmdaCIRMRateOverride
THsmdaCIRMRateOverride.description: The HSMDA CIR rate to be used in Mbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

TPIRRate.name: TPIRRate
TPIRRate.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THPolVirtualSchePIRRate.name: THPolVirtualSchePIRRate
THPolVirtualSchePIRRate.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THPolVirtualScheCIRRate.name: THPolVirtualScheCIRRate
THPolVirtualScheCIRRate.description: The CIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TAdvCfgRate.name: TAdvCfgRate
TAdvCfgRate.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps.

TMaxDecRate.name: TMaxDecRate
TMaxDecRate.description: The Advanced Configuration policy Max-Decrement rate to be used in kbps.

THPolPIRRate.name: THPolPIRRate
THPolPIRRate.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TSecondaryShaper10GPIRRate.name: TSecondaryShaper10GPIRRate
TSecondaryShaper10GPIRRate.description: The secondary shaper PIR rate to be used in Mbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TExpSecondaryShaperPIRRate.name: TExpSecondaryShaperPIRRate
TExpSecondaryShaperPIRRate.description: The expanded secondary shaper PIR rate to be used in Kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TExpSecondaryShaperClassRate.name: TExpSecondaryShaperClassRate
TExpSecondaryShaperClassRate.description: The expanded secondary shaper class PIR rate to be used in Kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

TPIRRateOverride.name: TPIRRateOverride
TPIRRateOverride.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

THPolPIRRateOverride.name: THPolPIRRateOverride
THPolPIRRateOverride.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

TPIRPercentOverride.name: TPIRPercentOverride
TPIRPercentOverride.description: The PIR percentage rate specified in hundredths of a percent. A value of -2 specifies no override.

TPIRRateOrZero.name: TPIRRateOrZero
TPIRRateOrZero.description: The PIR rate to be used in kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. The value 0 means undefined rate.

THsmdaPIRKRate.name: THsmdaPIRKRate
THsmdaPIRKRate.description: The HSMDA PIR rate to be used in Kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THsmdaPIRKRateOverride.name: THsmdaPIRKRateOverride
THsmdaPIRKRateOverride.description: The HSMDA PIR rate to be used in Kbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

THsmdaPIRMRate.name: THsmdaPIRMRate
THsmdaPIRMRate.description: The HSMDA PIR rate to be used in Mbps. The value -1 means maximum rate.

THsmdaPIRMRateOverride.name: THsmdaPIRMRateOverride
THsmdaPIRMRateOverride.description: The HSMDA PIR rate to be used in Mbps. The value -1 means maximum rate. A value of -2 specifies no override.

TmnxOspfInstance.name: TmnxOspfInstance
TmnxOspfInstance.description: A number used to identify an instance of OSPF.

TmnxBGPFamilyType.name: TmnxBGPFamilyType
TmnxBGPFamilyType.description: The value of TmnxBGPFamilyType specifies the AFI-SAFI family for BGP peer.

TmnxIgmpGroupFilterMode.name: TmnxIgmpGroupFilterMode
TmnxIgmpGroupFilterMode.description: The data type TmnxIgmpGroupFilterMode describes the filter-mode of a group. In 'include(1)' mode, reception of packets sent to the specified multicast address is requested only from those IPv4 Source addresses listed in the corresponding source-list. In 'exclude(2)' mode, reception of packets sent to the given multicast address is requested from all IPv4 Source addresses, except those listed in the corresponding source-list (if any).

TmnxIgmpGroupType.name: TmnxIgmpGroupType
TmnxIgmpGroupType.description: The data type TmnxIgmpGroupType describes how a multicast group is learned.

TmnxIgmpVersion.name: TmnxIgmpVersion
TmnxIgmpVersion.description: The data type TmnxIgmpVersion denotes the version of the IGMP protocol: - 'version1(1)': means version 1 of the IGMP protocol - 'version2(2)': means version 2 of the IGMP protocol - 'version3(3)': means version 3 of the IGMP protocol.

TmnxMldGroupFilterMode.name: TmnxMldGroupFilterMode
TmnxMldGroupFilterMode.description: The data type TmnxMldGroupFilterMode describes the filter-mode of a group. In 'include(1)' mode, reception of packets sent to the specified multicast address is requested only from those IPv6 source addresses listed in the corresponding source-list. In 'exclude(2)' mode, reception of packets sent to the given multicast address is requested from all IPv6 source addresses, except those listed in the corresponding source-list (if any).

TmnxMldGroupType.name: TmnxMldGroupType
TmnxMldGroupType.description: The data type TmnxMldGroupType describes how a multicast group is learned.

TmnxMldVersion.name: TmnxMldVersion
TmnxMldVersion.description: The data type TmnxMldVersion denotes the version of the MLD protocol: - 'version1(1)': means version 1 of the MLD protocol - 'version2(2)': means version 2 of the MLD protocol

TmnxManagedRouteStatus.name: TmnxManagedRouteStatus
TmnxManagedRouteStatus.description: The data type TmnxManagedRouteStatus denotes the status of a Managed Route.

TmnxAncpString.name: TmnxAncpString
TmnxAncpString.description: The TmnxAncpString data type contains a valid ancp string.

TmnxAncpStringOrZero.name: TmnxAncpStringOrZero
TmnxAncpStringOrZero.description: The TmnxAncpStringOrZero data type contains a valid ancp string. An empty string indicates that no ANCP string is defined.

TmnxMulticastAddrFamily.name: TmnxMulticastAddrFamily
TmnxMulticastAddrFamily.description: The data type TmnxMulticastAddrFamily denotes the family for multicast protocol.

TmnxAsciiSpecification.name: TmnxAsciiSpecification
TmnxAsciiSpecification.description: The data type TmnxAsciiSpecification is a format string that specifies how to form a target ASCII string. The format is as follows: <ascii-specification> ::= <char-specification>+ <char-specification> ::= <ascii-char> | <char-origin> <char-origin> ::= '%' <origin> <ascii-char> refers to a printable ASCII character. Examples and supported char-origin specifiers are supplied with the object definitions.

TmnxMacSpecification.name: TmnxMacSpecification
TmnxMacSpecification.description: The data type TmnxMacSpecification is a string of ASCII characters that specifies how to format a string that represents a MAC address. The format is as follows: <mac-specification> ::= <alpha-string> [<delimiter-char>] <alpha-string> ::= <ucase-alpha>+ | <lcase-alpha>+ <ucase-alpha> ::= 'A' | 'B' | 'B' ... | 'Z' <lcase-alpha> ::= 'a' | 'b' | 'c' ... | 'z' <delimiter-char> any ASCII character that is not an <alpha-char> or a decimal digit Only the number of alphabetic characters and the case is relevant. Examples: 'ab:' 00:0c:f1:99:85:b8 Alcatel-Lucent SROS style 'XY-' 00-0C-F1-99-85-B8 IEEE canonical style 'mmmm.' 0002.03aa.abff Cisco style. 'xx' 000cf19985b8

TmnxBinarySpecification.name: TmnxBinarySpecification
TmnxBinarySpecification.description: The data type TmnxBinarySpecification is a string of ASCII characters that specifies how to form a binary number. The format is as follows: <binary-specification> ::= <bit-specification>+ <bit-specification> ::= '0' | '1' | <bit-origin> <bit-origin> ::= '*' <number-of-bits> <origin> <number-of-bits> ::= [1..32] Examples and supported bit-origin specifiers are supplied with the object definitions.

TmnxDefSubIdSource.name: TmnxDefSubIdSource
TmnxDefSubIdSource.description: The data type TmnxDefSubIdSource specifies what will be used as the default subscriber identification. This value is used in case no other source (like RADIUS) provides a subscriber identification string. If the value of this object is set to 'useSapId', the SAP-id will be used as the default subscriber identification string. If the value of this object is set to 'useAutoId', the auto-generated subscriber identification string, as defined in tmnxSubMgmtAutoSubIdObjs, is used as the default subscriber identification string. If the value of this object is set to 'useString', the value of the string contained in another object will be used as the default subscriber identification string; that object must be identified where this datatype is used.

TmnxSubIdentString.name: TmnxSubIdentString
TmnxSubIdentString.description: The data type TmnxSubIdentString denotes the subscriber identification string.

TmnxSubIdentStringOrEmpty.name: TmnxSubIdentStringOrEmpty
TmnxSubIdentStringOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxSubIdentStringOrEmpty denotes the subscriber identification string. The empty string denotes the absence of a subscriber identification string.

TmnxSubRadServAlgorithm.name: TmnxSubRadServAlgorithm
TmnxSubRadServAlgorithm.description: The TmnxSubRadServAlgorithm data type is an enumerated integer that indicates the algorithm used to access the list of configured RADIUS servers: - direct (1): The first server will be used as primary server for all requests, the second as secondary and so on. - roundRobin (2): The first server will be used as primary server for the first request, the second server as primary for the second request, and so on. If the router gets to the end of the list, it starts again with the first server. - hashBased (3): The server will be selected based on a specified hash value.

TmnxSubRadiusAttrType.name: TmnxSubRadiusAttrType
TmnxSubRadiusAttrType.description: The TmnxSubRadiusAttrType data type contains a number that indicates a RADIUS attribute type.
TmnxSubRadiusAttrType.reference: RFC 2865 Remote Authentication Dial In User Service (RADIUS) section 5. Attributes

TmnxSubRadiusVendorId.name: TmnxSubRadiusVendorId
TmnxSubRadiusVendorId.description: The TmnxSubRadiusVendorId data type contains a number that indicates a RADIUS Vendor-Id.
TmnxSubRadiusVendorId.reference: RFC 2865 Remote Authentication Dial In User Service (RADIUS) section 5.26. Vendor-Specific.

TmnxRadiusPendingReqLimit.name: TmnxRadiusPendingReqLimit
TmnxRadiusPendingReqLimit.description: The TmnxRadiusPendingReqLimit data type is a number that specifies the limit to the number of pending RADIUS request messages.

TmnxRadiusServerOperState.name: TmnxRadiusServerOperState
TmnxRadiusServerOperState.description: The TmnxRadiusServerOperState data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the operational state of a RADIUS server.

TmnxSubProfileString.name: TmnxSubProfileString
TmnxSubProfileString.description: The data type TmnxSubProfileString denotes the subscriber profile string.

TmnxSubProfileStringOrEmpty.name: TmnxSubProfileStringOrEmpty
TmnxSubProfileStringOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxSubProfileStringOrEmpty denotes the subscriber profile string. The empty string denotes the absence of a subscriber profile.

TmnxSlaProfileString.name: TmnxSlaProfileString
TmnxSlaProfileString.description: The data type TmnxSlaProfileString denotes the SLA profile string.

TmnxSlaProfileStringOrEmpty.name: TmnxSlaProfileStringOrEmpty
TmnxSlaProfileStringOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxSlaProfileStringOrEmpty denotes the SLA profile string. The empty string denotes the absence of a SLA profile.

TmnxAppProfileString.name: TmnxAppProfileString
TmnxAppProfileString.description: The data type TmnxAppProfileString denotes the application profile string.

TmnxAppProfileStringOrEmpty.name: TmnxAppProfileStringOrEmpty
TmnxAppProfileStringOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxAppProfileStringOrEmpty denotes the application profile string. The empty string denotes the absence of a application profile.

TmnxSubMgtIntDestIdOrEmpty.name: TmnxSubMgtIntDestIdOrEmpty
TmnxSubMgtIntDestIdOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxSubMgtIntDestIdOrEmpty denotes the intermediate destination id. The empty string denotes the absence of an intermediate destination id.

TmnxSubMgtIntDestId.name: TmnxSubMgtIntDestId
TmnxSubMgtIntDestId.description: The data type TmnxSubMgtIntDestId denotes the intermediate destination id.

TmnxDefInterDestIdSource.name: TmnxDefInterDestIdSource
TmnxDefInterDestIdSource.description: The data type TmnxDefInterDestIdSource specifies what will be used as the default intermediate destination identifier. This value is used in case no other source (like RADIUS) provides an intermediate destination identifier. If the value of this object is set to 'useString', the value of the string contained in another object will be used as the default intermediate destination identifier; that object must be identified where this datatype is used. If the value of this object is set to 'useTopQTag', the top q-tag of the ingress SAP will be used as the default subscriber intermediate destination identifier. If the value of this object is set to 'useVpi', the ATM VPI of the ingress SAP will be used as the default subscriber intermediate destination identifier.

TmnxSubNasPortSuffixType.name: TmnxSubNasPortSuffixType
TmnxSubNasPortSuffixType.description: The TmnxSubNasPortSuffixType data type is an enumerated integer that specifies what suffix will be added to the RADIUS NAS-Port attribute: - none (0): No suffix will be added. - circuitId (1): If available, the circuit-id will be added. - remoteId (2): If available, the remote-id will be added.

TmnxSubNasPortPrefixType.name: TmnxSubNasPortPrefixType
TmnxSubNasPortPrefixType.description: The TmnxSubNasPortPrefixType data type is an enumerated integer that specifies what prefix will be added to the RADIUS NAS-Port attribute: - none (0): No prefix will be added. - userString (1): A user configurable string will be added.

TmnxSubNasPortTypeType.name: TmnxSubNasPortTypeType
TmnxSubNasPortTypeType.description: The TmnxSubNasPortTypeType data type is an enumerated integer that specifies what value will be put in the RADIUS NAS-Port-Type attribute: - standard (1): according to the RADIUS specification RFC 2865 section 5.41 NAS-Port-Type; - config (2): a configured value.

TmnxSubMgtOrgStrOrZero.name: TmnxSubMgtOrgStrOrZero
TmnxSubMgtOrgStrOrZero.description: The data type TmnxSubMgtOrgStrOrZero denotes the organization string. The empty string denotes the absence of an organization string.

TmnxSubMgtOrgString.name: TmnxSubMgtOrgString
TmnxSubMgtOrgString.description: The data type TmnxSubMgtOrgStrOrZero denotes the organization string.

TmnxFilterProfileStringOrEmpty.name: TmnxFilterProfileStringOrEmpty
TmnxFilterProfileStringOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxFilterProfileStringOrEmpty denotes the filter profile string. The empty string denotes the absence of a filter profile.

TmnxAccessLoopEncapDataLink.name: TmnxAccessLoopEncapDataLink
TmnxAccessLoopEncapDataLink.description: The data type TmnxAccessLoopEncapDataLink specifies the data link used by the subscriber on the DSL access loop.

TmnxAccessLoopEncaps1.name: TmnxAccessLoopEncaps1
TmnxAccessLoopEncaps1.description: The data type TmnxAccessLoopEncaps1 specifies the encapsulation used by the subscriber on the DSL access loop.

TmnxAccessLoopEncaps2.name: TmnxAccessLoopEncaps2
TmnxAccessLoopEncaps2.description: The data type TmnxAccessLoopEncaps2 specifies the encapsulation used by the subscriber on the DSL access loop.

TmnxSubAleOffsetMode.name: TmnxSubAleOffsetMode
TmnxSubAleOffsetMode.description: The data type TmnxSubAleOffsetMode specifies the way the encapsulation offset of the subscriber in the DSL access loop is learned by the 7xxx system. This offset is used in 7xxx egress shaping, adjusting the subscriber aggregate rate to account for the fixed encapsulation offset and per packet variable expansion of the last mile for the specific session used by the subscriber host. The value 'none' disables the adjustment. While the value is 'auto', the encapsulation offset will be learned for example from the encapsulation type value signaled in the Access-loop-encapsulation sub-TLV in the Vendor-Specific PPPoE Tags or DHCP Relay Options [rfc4679].

TmnxSubAleOffset.name: TmnxSubAleOffset
TmnxSubAleOffset.description: The data type TmnxSubAleOffset specifies the encapsulation offset value of the subscriber in the DSL access loop as used by the 7xxx system. This offset is used in 7xxx egress shaping in order to accurately shape the end user payload.

TmnxDhcpOptionType.name: TmnxDhcpOptionType
TmnxDhcpOptionType.description: The data type TmnxDhcpOptionType represents how the value of this option is encoded: - 'ipv4 (1)' : this option contains an IPv4 address (4 octets) - 'ascii(2)' : this option contains seven-bit ASCII characters - 'hex (3)' : this option contains octets. It must be displayed in hexadecimal format because it contains non-printable characters. - 'ipv6 (4)' : this option contains an IPv6 address (16 octets) - 'domain (5)': this option contains a domain name that will be encoded as specified by RFC 1035 section 3.1.

TmnxPppoeUserName.name: TmnxPppoeUserName
TmnxPppoeUserName.description: The data type TmnxPppoeUserName denotes the PPPoE username.

TmnxPppoeUserNameOrEmpty.name: TmnxPppoeUserNameOrEmpty
TmnxPppoeUserNameOrEmpty.description: The data type TmnxPppoeUserNameOrEmpty denotes the PPPoE username.

TCpmProtPolicyID.name: TCpmProtPolicyID
TCpmProtPolicyID.description: The data type TCpmProtPolicyID represents the identification number of a CPM Protection policy. The value '0' indicates that no CPM Protection policy is provisioned.

TCpmProtPolicyIDOrDefault.name: TCpmProtPolicyIDOrDefault
TCpmProtPolicyIDOrDefault.description: The data type TCpmProtPolicyIDOrDefault represents the identification number of a CPM Protection policy. The value of '-1' indicates the system determined default value.

TMlpppQoSProfileId.name: TMlpppQoSProfileId
TMlpppQoSProfileId.description: This textual-convention uniquely identifies MLPPP Bundle QoS profile in the ingress and egress MLPPP QoS profile tables. The value 0 indicates default MLPPP QoS Profile as applicable to a given H/W

TMcFrQoSProfileId.name: TMcFrQoSProfileId
TMcFrQoSProfileId.description: This textual-convention uniquely identifies Multi-class Frame-relay QoS profiles in the ingress and egress multi-class frame-relay QoS profile tables. The value 0 indicates a default QoS Profile as applicable to a given hardware.

TmnxPppoeSessionId.name: TmnxPppoeSessionId
TmnxPppoeSessionId.description: The TmnxPppoeSessionId indicates the 16 bit wide PPPoE session Id.

TmnxPppoePadoDelay.name: TmnxPppoePadoDelay
TmnxPppoePadoDelay.description: The data type TmnxPppoePadoDelay specifies the delay timeout in deci-seconds before sending a PADO (PPPoE Active Discovery Offer).

TmnxPppoeSessionInfoOrigin.name: TmnxPppoeSessionInfoOrigin
TmnxPppoeSessionInfoOrigin.description: The TmnxPppoeSessionInfoOrigin indicates the originator of the provided information.

TmnxPppoeSessionType.name: TmnxPppoeSessionType
TmnxPppoeSessionType.description: The TmnxPppoeSessionType indicates the type of PPPoE session.

TmnxPppNcpProtocol.name: TmnxPppNcpProtocol
TmnxPppNcpProtocol.description: The TmnxPppNcpProtocol data type represents the PPP Network Control Protocol.

TmnxMlpppEpClass.name: TmnxMlpppEpClass
TmnxMlpppEpClass.description: The TmnxMlpppEpClass type represents the address class of the MLPPP Endpoint Discriminator option.

TNetworkPolicyID.name: TNetworkPolicyID
TNetworkPolicyID.description: the identification number of a network policy.

TItemScope.name: TItemScope
TItemScope.description: This textual-convention determines some aspects of an item's behavior regarding creation and use, unused entry garbage collection, and automated promulgation by Element Management System to other systems in the service domain. TItemScope applies to SAP-ingress, SAP-egress, and Network policies, and to IP filters and MAC filters. exclusive: When the scope of an item is defined as exclusive, the item can only be applied once, for example to a single SAP. Attempting to assign the policy to a second SAP is not allowed and will result in an error. If the item is removed from the exclusive SAP, it will become available for assignment to another exclusive SAP. A non-applied exclusive scope policy is a candidate to be removed from the system by a TBD garbage collection command. The system default policies cannot be put into the exclusive scope. An error will be generated if scope exclusive is executed in any policies with a policy-id equal to 1. template: When the scope of an item is defined as template, the item can be applied any number of times. Policies with template scope will not be considered for deletion by a TBD garbage collection command; all items of scope 'template' must be deleted explicitly. The system default policies will always be scope template. An error will occur if a policy-id 1 is attempted to be set to scope exclusive.

TItemMatch.name: TItemMatch
TItemMatch.description: when set to off, the item is not matched. when set to false, packets without the item match the filter. when set to true, packets with the item match the filter.

TPriority.name: TPriority
TPriority.description: the priority to apply to a packet

TPriorityOrDefault.name: TPriorityOrDefault
TPriorityOrDefault.description: the priority to apply to a packet. when set to default(3), the priority from the default-action is used.

TProfileUseDEOrNone.name: TProfileUseDEOrNone
TProfileUseDEOrNone.description: This textual-convention specifies the profile marking of a packet. Value of 'in' specifies in-profile marking. Value of 'out' specifies out-profile marking. Value of 'de' specifies that the profile marking of the packet will be based on the DE (Drop-Eligible) bit of the packet. DE bit value of '0' specifies in-profile and DE bit value of '1' specifies out-profile marking. Value of 'none' specifies the profile marking of the packet will be inherited from the existing enqueuing priority derived from earlier matches in the classification hierarchy.

TPriorityOrUndefined.name: TPriorityOrUndefined
TPriorityOrUndefined.description: the priority to apply to a packet. when set to undefined(0), the priority is not applicable.

TProfile.name: TProfile
TProfile.description: the profile marking of a packet at the ingress.

TProfileOrDei.name: TProfileOrDei
TProfileOrDei.description: the profile marking of a packet at the ingress.

TDEProfile.name: TDEProfile
TDEProfile.description: This textual-convention specifies the profile marking of a packet. Value of 'in' specifies the in-profile marking. Value of 'out' specifies the out-profile marking. Value of 'de' specifies that the profile marking will be based on the DE (Drop-Eligible) bit. DE bit-value of '0' specifies in-profile and DE bit value of '1' specifies out-profile marking.

TDEProfileOrDei.name: TDEProfileOrDei
TDEProfileOrDei.description: This textual-convention specifies the profile marking of a packet. Value of 'in' specifies the in-profile marking. Value of 'out' specifies the out-profile marking. Value of 'de' specifies that the profile marking will be based on the DE (Drop-Eligible) bit. DE bit-value of '0' specifies in-profile and DE bit value of '1' specifies out-profile marking.

TAdaptationRule.name: TAdaptationRule
TAdaptationRule.description: The adaptation rule to be applied to calcluate the operational values for the specified entity.

TAdaptationRuleOverride.name: TAdaptationRuleOverride
TAdaptationRuleOverride.description: The adaptation rule to be applied to calcluate the operational values for the specified entity.

TPrecValue.name: TPrecValue

TQueueMode.name: TQueueMode
TQueueMode.description: The mode in which the queue is operating. If the queue is operating in the 'priority' mode, it is capable of handling traffic differently with two distinct priorities. These priorities are assigned by the stages preceding the queueing framework in the system. When the queue is operating in the 'profile' mode, in other words the color aware mode, the queue tries to provide the appropriate bandwidth to the packets with different profiles. The profiles are assigned according to the configuration of the forwarding class or the sub-forwarding class. In 'priority' mode, the queue does not have the functionality to support the profiled traffic and in such cases the queue will have a degraded performance. However, the converse is not valid and a queue in 'profile' mode should be capable of supporting the different priorities of traffic.

TMatchCriteria.name: TMatchCriteria

TmnxMdaQos.name: TmnxMdaQos

TAtmTdpDescrType.name: TAtmTdpDescrType
TAtmTdpDescrType.description: The TAtmTdpDescrType is an enumerated integer whose value indicates the types of cell loss priority to be used in conjunction with traffic parameters. The following values are outlined: Integer Value Interpretation ------------- ------------------------ clp0And1pcr PCR applies to CLP 0 and CLP 1 cell flows clp0And1pcrPlusClp0And1scr PCR applies to CLP 0 and CLP 1 cell flows. A value of 'hybrid' indicates that the FCC server will use combination of 'burst' and 'dent' to send the unicast stream to the client. A value of 'none' indicates that FCC server is disabled.

TmnxMobImsi.name: TmnxMobImsi
TmnxMobImsi.description: The data type TmnxMobImsi describes the International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI) of an User Equipment (UE). IMSI is defined as a number consisting of up to 15 BCD digits. The first 3 digits are the Mobile Country Code (MCC). The next 2 or 3 digits are the Mobile Network Code (MNC). The value of MCC determines whether the MNC is 2 digits or 3 digits. The remaining digits are the Mobile Subscriber Identification Number (MSIN). The internal representation of the IMSI is as follows: Bits 63-62 are reserved. Bits 61-60 indicate the length of the MNC field: 10 indicates a 2-digit MNC while 11 indicates a 3-digit MNC. Bits 59-0 hold the 15 IMSI BCD digits D1-15. When the total number of digits in the IMSI is less than 15, the nibble 0xf is used a filler. IMSI encoding for a 2-digit MNC: 63 55 47 39 0 +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ | 0010| MCC1| MCC2| MCC3| MNC1| MNC2| MSIN (up to 10 digits) +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ IMSI encoding for a 3-digit MNC: 63 55 47 39 35 0 +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ | 0011| MCC1| MCC2| MCC3| MNC1| MNC2| MNC3| MSIN (up to 9 digits) +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ Bits 63-56 of the IMSI are carried in octet number 1 of the octet string and bits 7-0 are carried in octet number 8 of the octet string.

TmnxMobMsisdn.name: TmnxMobMsisdn

TmnxMobImei.name: TmnxMobImei

TmnxMobNai.name: TmnxMobNai

Bits 59-0 hold the 15 IMSI BCD digits D1-15. When the total number of digits in the IMSI is less than 15, the nibble 0xf is used a filler. IMSI encoding for a 2-digit MNC: 63 55 47 39 0 +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ | 0010| MCC1| MCC2| MCC3| MNC1| MNC2| MSIN (up to 10 digits) +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ IMSI encoding for a 3-digit MNC: 63 55 47 39 35 0 +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ | 0011| MCC1| MCC2| MCC3| MNC1| MNC2| MNC3| MSIN (up to 9 digits) +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ Bits 63-56 of the IMSI are carried in octet number 1 of the octet string and bits 7-0 are carried in octet number 8 of the octet string.

Setting a variable of this type to 'none' indicates no error level. A value of 'tnc' indicates a TNC (Tech Non-Conformance) error level.A value of 'qos' indicates a QOS (Quality of Service) error level. A value of 'poa' indicates a POA (Program off Air) error level.

TmnxVdoAnalyzerAlarmStates.name: TmnxVdoAnalyzerAlarmStates
TmnxVdoAnalyzerAlarmStates.description: The data type TmnxVdoAnalyzerAlarmStates is an octet string that represents the analyzer state for the past 10 seconds. Setting a variable of this type to 'good'(00) indicates either there was no alarm during that second or the state of the stream has been cleared from a prior errored state. A value of 'tnc'(01)indicates a TNC (Tech Non-Conformance) error occured during that second. A value of 'qos'(02) indicates a QOS (Quality of Service) error occured during that second. A value of 'poa'(03) indicates a POA (Program off Air) error occured during that second. Since the octet string is 10 bytes long, the 10th byte indicates the most recent state of the stream. Below is how an example stream would appear. Each byte in the stream holds an alarm state for a second. good (00), -- stream was good during 1st second tnc (01), -- stream had tnc error during 2nd second qos (02), -- stream had qos error during 3rd second qos (02), -- stream had qos error during 4th second qos (02), -- stream had qos error during 5th second good (00), -- stream error was cleared during 6th second good (00), -- stream was good during 7th second tnc (01), -- stream had tnc error during 8nd second poa (03), -- stream had poa error during 9th second good (00) -- stream error was cleared during 10th second.

TmnxMobUeId.name: TmnxMobUeId
TmnxMobUeId.description: The data type TmnxMobUeId describes the identity of an User Equipment. TmnxMobUeId can be of the following types: International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI), International Mobile station Equipment Identity (IMEI), Mobile Subscriber Integrated Services Digital network Number (MSISDN). IMSI, IMEI, MSISDN are defined in 3GPP TS 23.003. IMSI is defined as a number consisting of up to 15 BCD digits. The first 3 digits are the Mobile Country Code (MCC). The next 2 or 3 digits are the Mobile Network Code (MNC). The value of MCC determines whether the MNC is 2 digits or 3 digits. The remaining digits are the Mobile Subscriber Identification Number (MSIN). IMEI is defined as a number consisting of up to 16 BCD digits. The first 8 digits consists of Type Allocation Code (TAC). The next 6 digits consist of Serial Number (SNR) which could be followed by a Check Digit (CD) or Spare Digit (SD) of size 1 digit or by a Software Version Number (SVN) of size 2 digits. MSISDN is defined as a number consisting of 9 to 15 BCD digits. MSISDN consists of Country Code (CC) followed by National Destination Code (NDC) and Subscriber Number (SN). Bits 63-56 of the IMSI or IMEI or MSISDN are carried in octet number 1 of the octet string and bits 7-0 are carried in octet number 8 of the octet string. The internal representation of the IMSI is as follows: Bits 63-62 are reserved. Bits 61-60 indicate the length of the MNC field: 10 indicates a 2-digit MNC while 11 indicates a 3-digit MNC. Bits 59-0 hold the 15 IMSI BCD digits D1-15. When the total number of digits in the IMSI is less than 15, the nibble 0xf is used a filler. IMSI encoding for a 2-digit MNC: 63 55 47 39 0 +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ | 0010| MCC1| MCC2| MCC3| MNC1| MNC2| MSIN (up to 10 digits) +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ IMSI encoding for a 3-digit MNC: 63 55 47 39 35 0 +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ | 0011| MCC1| MCC2| MCC3| MNC1| MNC2| MNC3| MSIN (up to 9 digits) +-----------+-----------+-----------+-------------------------+ The internal representation of the IMEI and MSISDN is as follows: IMEI encoding: 63 55 31 7 0 +-----------+-----------+----------------------+-------+ | TAC | SNR | SNV | |N2|N1|N4|N3|N6|N5|N8|N7|N10|N9|N12|N11|N14|N13|N16|N15| +-----------+-----------+-----------+------------------+ MSISDN encoding: 63 55 31 7 0 +-----------+-----------+----------------------+-------+ | CC | NDC | SN | |N2|N1|N4|N3|N6|N5|N8|N7|N10|N9|N12|N11|N14|N13|N16|N15| +-----------+-----------+-----------+------------------+ When the total number of digits in the IMEI or MSISDN is less than 15, the nibble 0x0 is used a filler. In each byte both nibbles are swapped and it is stored as shown in the above format. For example, in the format N3 & N4 present the nibble number 3 and 4 respectively and they are stored in reverse order. When the total number of digits are odd in IMEI and MSISDB, the last digit will be paired with nibble 0xf.
